{# What we believe #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="what-we-believe" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>What We Believe</h2>
    <p>Good driving schools need more than just leads. They need admin, systems, structure, compliance, marketing, and real support behind the scenes. A great instructor and a good local reputation are the heart of a school, but on their own they are not enough to keep the business running smoothly week after week.</p>
    <p>The schools that thrive over time are the ones with a proper operating backbone. Building that backbone is what we do, and it is why owners and instructors come to us.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# Our values #}
<section class="section section--light" id="our-values">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 data-animate="fade-up">Our Values</h2>
    <ul class="values-list" data-stagger>
      <li><strong>Quality.</strong> We hold ourselves, and the brands we operate, to high standards for instruction, admin, and customer experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Continuity.</strong> When we acquire a driving school, we protect the brand, the instructors, the customers, and the trust they have built together.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency.</strong> We operate openly with owners, instructors, agencies, and learners. We say what we mean.</li>
      <li><strong>Long-term thinking.</strong> We are building over years, not running a campaign for a quarter. Every decision is made with that horizon in mind.</li>
      <li><strong>Practical support.</strong> We help the schools and instructors in our group with the work that actually slows them down: admin, bookings, marketing, compliance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

